Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: If you’re using Ethereum and storing metadata on it, won’t it bloat the network? A: The simple answer to that is no. Due to the semantic infrastructure of WRIO Internet OS, the metadata will equal ‘tags’ on the blockchain, and these tags will be limited to <64 bytes only, and every post on the platform, for instance, has a “wallet” attached to it with a list of transactions and metadata (tags). To put this in perspective, Wikipedia has about 5 million articles and the whole ETH transaction capacity is about .5 million per day. That means the whole wiki metadata equal to 10 days of ETH capacity only.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: Who can use WRIO Internet OS, and why? A: WRIO Internet OS was created to be an alternative to today’s Web 2.0 — cluttered, non-secure, and with large scale privacy breaches almost daily on the news. The purpose of this project is for everyone to benefit from a user-centric browsing experience utilizing the semantic web with automatic data processing and storing metadata on the large degree of security that a blockchain brings. Authors, Entrepreneurs, Developers, and Users will all be incentivized to bring WRIO Internet OS to its end goal, what we call The Alternative.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: What is the current state of the WRIO Internet OS project? A: The MVP was launched in April 2018 and we’re on schedule (see Roadmap) to further develop the project to the point where we can soon bring a generation of fully distributed and secure Web 3.0 browsing.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: How does WRIO Internet OS utilize the blockchain? A: Blockchain technology will be utilized to store the metadata of each generated page prior to being integrated to the user’s Interest Matrix compiled in their profile. It helps in the process of linking decentralized pages through a global metadatabase.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: Why are you using Ethereum? A: Ethereum has matured dramatically over the past few years, and we’re thankful for the Ethereum team’s efforts for that. Because of its maturity and therefore it’s blockchain security, as well as it’s scaling capability plans, we believe it’s the best option for us to run this platform on.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: If you’re using Ethereum and storing metadata on it, won’t it bloat the network? A: The simple answer to that is no. Due to the semantic infrastructure of WRIO Internet OS, the metadata will equal ‘tags’ on the blockchain, and these tags will be limited to <64 bytes only, and every post (such as an author post-link) on the platform, for instance, has a “wallet” attached it with a list of transactions.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Dashboard is going to be like a chrome startup page were you can manage your bookmarks and streams. Streams are like a facebook feed: here you'll see all content filtered by your Interests Matrix. So it's kind a global subscription by tags. E.x. you may be interested in dogs (but only in pekingeses and bulldogs but not poodles) and get a proper content with tags pekingese and/or bulldog if the content has enough rating level to be displayed on your web dashboard.  You can use any device while it has access to you CryptoKey. But at the moment we have a limited cloud MVP version only to demonstrate semantic pages creation and Crediting (https://wrioos.com/#Credits): we'll answer on your quesdtion #2 a bit later.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: WGD is a token required for settlements between WRIO Internet OS projects. Every WRIO OS app can have own token to operate, like Gas is needed for Ethereum work. Credit is native WRIO OS token. Why. Own tokens needed to control inner app economy. So app tokens is like shop coupons - as a shop owner you can't control $, but you can issue coupons usable inside your shop. So, you can issue your own tokens and reward your users via it. More tokens you issue -> less WGD exhange rate its have.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Thanks for your interest!   Your profile is the history of transaction records, in other words: it's stored in the blockchain (private data is encrypted), thus you can change, lose or break your device, it's nothing more than just a terminal. Just be sure you keep save your CryptoKey to be able to get access to your profile from any other device. BTW, you can split (it will be an automatic process, you just need to chose your trusted key keepers) your CryptoKey between friends: e.x., you can use "3 of 10" or other schema, like AWS do with data storage. "3 of 10" means, you splited your key between 10 friends and it's enough to get in touch any 3 of them to restore your key. You can add additinal security layer and secure the process with a password. Let us know if you have more questions, we'd love to share!

Author: ePesoInitiative
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Well, that's an entirely different story right there. There used to be a button similar to Facebook "likes" where the author of an article gets paid with every "like". I forgot the name, but it didn't pan out and died.  Most people like freemium services and sacrifice their privacy for it.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Correct. It's not original functionality. But this is only the beginning of the story. Imagine that you get those non-flat likes (for free) and from others (for your posts), to be able to say "+" for content you like. System collects not just likes, but amount of them. E.x. you like kitties (e.x. 2CRD is your median kitties "likes") and you give more Credits for dog posts (5CRD is your median "like"). And besides that: dog->bulldog (7CRD median) and dog->poodle (0 CRD). All this info help system to "understand" your interests precisely and help to buld your Interest Matrix. All those transactions stored in the blockchain and open for everyone. But we're a privacy respect service, your transaction can be open, but your profile can be anonymous or you can open your private info (encrypted) only for a few (give them access to the the key to un-encrypt, all in auto mode. Just click one button). That opens the door to the user-centric services: anyone can build his/her services, and we have the same blockchain access like others.  You can sell CRD for WGD, so its have value and you're spending them wisely enough. That helps to avoid spam effectivly. Please find more in the WhitePaper. There's a lot of information.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: WRIO OS works fine without ETH blockchain. Blockchain is only for additional features like metadata storage (for new kind of search engines), payments, Rating and so on. But once again: basic functionality rely on static pages in JSON-LD format and ETH blockchain is the optional layer above.  Please find our previous answer to get more information Quote You can try our MVP with any browser. Open view-source:https://wrioos.com/ to check the code. And even create your own machine-readable (in Linked Data format) page https://core.wrioos.com/create Note: editor is still in progress and has issues, sorry. We're working on it.  Web 3.0 browser will simply have more additional features.  To learn more about our vision of Web 3.0, check out our demo https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fd-wMXkJxb4  Demo uses another UI theme and shows functionality that will be available later.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: Will this affect the processing speed of the browser in getting the required information as it is using an isolated container? Will this requires higher ISP bandwidth speed? A: No, it's not. Isolated container does not affect browsing experience. In fact, getting pure data (JSON-LD) without html markup, css and js on the page reduces the bandwidth requirements. The average page (w/o images) is about ~20kb, so you can navigate very quickly.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Thanks! Please send your questions.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Q: how is this going to resolve the design interface if cant load the css and js? A: For WRIO Internet browser, browser plugin or mobile app it's like a default google chrome theme that can change on another. Or like you have the same facebook UI for all pages, but our variant is global and without vendor lockup and you'll be able to choose or develop you own theme. Yes, you have to download theme (markup+ css + js) by using WRIO OS node (e.x. load https://wrioos.com itself), but after that you use browser cache to render any other hubs: https://webrunes.com, https://aa.wr.io or created by you https://core.wrioos.com/create (sorry for any issues, still in dev). Or you can edit https[Suspicious link removed]yAnshakov/aa.wr.io-WRIO-Hub in any text editor. just upload on any static server and enjoy your own hub.

Author: webRunesTeam
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Modern browsers support HTML5 offline features, we're going to use them heavily. Naturally, WRIO OS node is using JS, but you can run your own WRIO OS server (open-source, you can use any of them like tor, they're only the gate and don't store any private data) and later we're going to develop WRIO OS browser, FF/Chrome plugins and mobile app: any of those stuff will take care about rendering pages and you won't need WRIO OS nodes any more. You can imagine them as read-only browser (all scripts are ignored) with apps (like plugins for browsers): sharing, commenting, funds transferring, you name it. You choose only what you do need for a comfortable browsing. You choose what features must be on the pages, not websites owners, they provide info/data only.

Author: webRunes
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Quote The Ricardian contract is a method of recording a document as a contract at law, and linking it securely to other systems, such as the accounting system, for the contract as an issuance of value Sure, but we'd like to make some notes. The purpose of RC is to create a machine-readable format for agreements, contracts and so on based on blockchain. We hunt for a different purpose: we'd like to create a platform to upgrade a human-redable web to a human&machine-readable web. We need blockcain only to store meta-data + url of pages based on machine-readable format, like a global decentralized HDD with docs that can be used by everybody (private data is encrypted). Imagine a global directory with data can be processed by machines: you don't need to search the web to find new content, you will get info automatically based on your Interest Matrix, like if you had dug the whole web and chose what to read by yourself. And this feature is only first what a machine-readable web can offer.

Author: webRunes
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: There isn’t any simple answer to that. Instead, there is a set of mutually complementary approaches. Each one of them requires an individual explanation, which can also be found in the White Paper. However, in brief, it is a possibility to support favorite authors: Credits (non-flat likes) for interesting content https://wrioos.com/#Credits. In turn, Crediting is directly related to reputation (Rating), which can be monetized. You can find detailed description of the process in Offers https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UM29XhlQ6ZsaWOWhIP5o4_Wh0m8Iy5NtL1-ia7z5aXQ/edit#heading=h.swddvye9h53m. Offers represent a precisely targeted approach that differs from ads by the following reasons: 1. it is viewed voluntarily, the advertiser may offer compensation for your time and attention; more details in the WP 2. the Offers’ purpose is to divert the direction of advertising. If now it is spam convincing us to buy something, then Offers are and answer to your need in solving a pressing issue: which footwear is better for jogging at a stadium? What smartphone will be better to purchase if I need one: [the list of your criteria] What cosmetics /clothes will fit you better considering the peculiarities of your body. Etc. All this is meant to radically change to the ads currently used in the web and reasonably blocked by people who do not wish to waste their time and attention to spam, even if the service or author have received payment for it.

Author: webRunes
Title: [ANN]An automatic data processing "Google"
Body: Browsing through pages in the google, yahoo, duckduckgo search engines (likely multiple times), and landing on pages with ads until you find what you’re looking for is the norm now—  Instead WRIO OS will be a semantic platform, so finding what you need from the web will be instantaneous as well as “user-centric” which means that based on your general usage, the data you’ll see will be unique to you— it will be inherently secure, and you’ll have a unique customizable dashboard— again thanks to its semantic nature, all data is there in front of you, all you have to do is theoretically look at it by either swiping, clicking a button or turning the page.  I.e no need to hop from one point to another as you do now ex. Yahoo.com to Reddit.com.
